title: High school football rankings for Oct. 13, 2015
text:
By Greg Joyce | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 13, 2015 11:00 AM, updated October 13, 2015 5:13 PM View/Post Comments 
Down went No. 1. 
The Liberty football team knocked off Parkland on Friday night to send a shockwave through the rankings. With the win, the Hurricanes (5-1) moved up to the No. 2 spot, their highest ranking this year. 
The only team above them is their crosstown rival, Freedom , which is the only unbeaten team left in the EPC. 
The Trojans slide down to No. 3, followed by Central Catholic , which ran past Nazareth on Saturday afternoon to knock the Blue Eagles from their perch at No. 3. 
Easton , which has a showdown with Parkland on Friday night, comes in at No. 5 after a blowout win over Whitehall . Nazareth fills in at No. 6. 
The rest of the Top 10 took care of business with wins.
